org.seedstack.business.domain

Interface AggregateRoot<I>

  • Type Parameters:
    I - the type of the aggregate root identifier.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Entity<I>, Producible
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BaseAggregateRoot

    @DomainAggregateRoot
public interface AggregateRoot<I>
extends Entity<I>, Producible
    Specialization of Entity when acting as an aggregate root.

    The BaseAggregateRoot class can be used as a base class for aggregate roots. It provides an implementation of the Entity.getId(), Entity.equals(Object) and Entity.hashCode() methods.

    See Also:
    DomainAggregateRoot, Entity

    • Method Summary

      • Methods inherited from interface org.seedstack.business.domain.Entity

        equals, getId, hashCode
